      "id": "block_1",
      "type": "text",
      "latex": "On considère la fonction $f$ définie sur $\\R$ par \n$$f(x)=\\begin{cases} \\lambda x & \\text{ si } x\\in[0,1] \\\\  \n        0 &\\text{ si } x\\notin [0,1].\n       \\end{cases}\n$$",
      "html": "<p>On considère la fonction <span>\\(f\\)</span> définie sur <span>\\(\\R\\)</span> par\n<span>\\[f(x)=\\begin{cases} \\lambda x &amp; \\text{ si } x\\in[0,1] \\\\  \n        0 &amp;\\text{ si } x\\notin [0,1].\n       \\end{cases}\\]</span></p>",
      "order": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "block_2",
      "type": "question",
      "latex": "Calculer $\\lambda$ pour que $f$ soit la densité d'une variable aléatoire absolument continue $X$.",
      "html": "<p>Calculer <span>\\(\\lambda\\)</span> pour que <span>\\(f\\)</span> soit la densité d’une variable aléatoire absolument continue <span>\\(X\\)</span>.</p>",
      "order": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "block_3",
      "type": "reponse",
      "latex": "Pour que $f$ soit une densité, il faut que $f$ soit positive sur $\\R$ (ce qui est le cas ici) et que $\\int_\\R f(x) \\dx =1$. Or\n \\[ \\int_\\R f(x) \\dx=\\int_0^1 \\lambda x \\dx  =\\left[ \\frac{\\lambda}{2}x^2\\right]_0^1 =\\frac{\\lambda}{2}\\]\n donc $\\lambda=2$.",
      "html": "<p>Pour que <span>\\(f\\)</span> soit une densité, il faut que <span>\\(f\\)</span> soit positive sur <span>\\(\\R\\)</span> (ce qui est le cas ici) et que <span>\\(\\int_\\R f(x) \\dx =1\\)</span>. Or\n<span>\\[\\int_\\R f(x) \\dx=\\int_0^1 \\lambda x \\dx  =\\left[ \\frac{\\lambda}{2}x^2\\right]_0^1 =\\frac{\\lambda}{2}\\]</span>\ndonc <span>\\(\\lambda=2\\)</span>.</p>",
      "order": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "block_4",
      "type": "question",
      "latex": "Déterminer $\\prob\\left(X\\leq \\frac{1}{3}\\right)$ et $\\prob\\left(X\\leq \\frac{2}{3} \\mid X>\\frac{1}{3}\\right)$.",
      "html": "<p>Déterminer <span>\\(\\prob\\left(X\\leq \\frac{1}{3}\\right)\\)</span> et <span>\\(\\prob\\left(X\\leq \\frac{2}{3} \\mid X&gt;\\frac{1}{3}\\right)\\)</span>.</p>",
      "order": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "block_5",
      "type": "reponse",
      "latex": "$$\\begin{align*}\n  &\\prob\\left(X\\leq \\frac{1}{3}\\right)=\\int_{-\\infty}^\\frac{1}{3} f(x)\\dx =[x^2]_0^\\frac{1}{3}=\\frac{1}{9} \\\\\n  &\\prob\\left(X\\leq \\frac{2}{3} \\mid X>\\frac{1}{3}\\right)=\\frac{\\prob\\left(\\frac{1}{3}<X\\leq \\frac{2}{3}\\right)}{\\prob\\left(X>\\frac{1}{3}\\right)}\n  = \\frac{\\int_\\frac{1}{3}^\\frac{2}{3}2x \\dx}{1-\\prob\\left(X\\leq \\frac{1}{3}\\right)}\n  =\\frac{[x^2]_\\frac{1}{3}^\\frac{2}{3}}{1-\\frac{1}{9}}\n  = \\frac{\\frac{1}{3}}{\\frac{8}{9}}\n  =\\frac{3}{8}\n \\end{align*}$$",
      "html": "<p><span>\\[\\begin{align*}\n  &amp;\\prob\\left(X\\leq \\frac{1}{3}\\right)=\\int_{-\\infty}^\\frac{1}{3} f(x)\\dx =[x^2]_0^\\frac{1}{3}=\\frac{1}{9} \\\\\n  &amp;\\prob\\left(X\\leq \\frac{2}{3} \\mid X&gt;\\frac{1}{3}\\right)=\\frac{\\prob\\left(\\frac{1}{3}&lt;X\\leq \\frac{2}{3}\\right)}{\\prob\\left(X&gt;\\frac{1}{3}\\right)}\n  = \\frac{\\int_\\frac{1}{3}^\\frac{2}{3}2x \\dx}{1-\\prob\\left(X\\leq \\frac{1}{3}\\right)}\n  =\\frac{[x^2]_\\frac{1}{3}^\\frac{2}{3}}{1-\\frac{1}{9}}\n  = \\frac{\\frac{1}{3}}{\\frac{8}{9}}\n  =\\frac{3}{8}\n \\end{align*}\\]</span></p>",
      "order": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "block_6",
      "type": "question",
      "latex": "Calculer $\\E(X)$ et $\\var(X)$.",
      "html": "<p>Calculer <span>\\(\\E(X)\\)</span> et <span>\\(\\var(X)\\)</span>.</p>",
      "order": 6
    },
    {
      "id": "block_7",
      "type": "reponse",
      "latex": "$$\\E(X)=\\int_\\R xf(x)\\dx =\\int_0^1 2x^2 \\dx =\\left[ \\frac{2}{3}x^3\\right]_0^1=\\frac{2}{3}$$\n $$\\begin{align*}\n  \\var(X) &= \\E(X^2)-\\E(X)^2\n  = \\int_\\R x^2f(x)\\dx  -\\left(\\frac{2}{3}\\right)^2 \n  = \\left[ \\frac{1}{2}x^4\\right]_0^1-\\frac{4}{9}\n  =\\frac{1}{2}-\\frac{4}{9}\n  =\\frac{1}{18}\n \\end{align*}$$",
      "html": "<p><span>\\[\\E(X)=\\int_\\R xf(x)\\dx =\\int_0^1 2x^2 \\dx =\\left[ \\frac{2}{3}x^3\\right]_0^1=\\frac{2}{3}\\]</span>\n<span>\\[\\begin{align*}\n  \\var(X) &amp;= \\E(X^2)-\\E(X)^2\n  = \\int_\\R x^2f(x)\\dx  -\\left(\\frac{2}{3}\\right)^2 \n  = \\left[ \\frac{1}{2}x^4\\right]_0^1-\\frac{4}{9}\n  =\\frac{1}{2}-\\frac{4}{9}\n  =\\frac{1}{18}\n \\end{align*}\\]</span></p>",
      "order": 7
    }
  ],
